reviews.review_text: This sounds really good Up front sound, nice presence and clarity, bass is even good.  Thanks to Tom for deciding to share this one. A terrific pull of a fun show!

I mostly avoid Auds I mostly avoid audience recordings. Each to his own. This is a fantastic recording however. I have just stremed my way through Cassidy and the songs are quite jamming put punctual. Not many missed notes at all. The Loser is fantastic with Phil im his irreverent fashion. Thanks for the Recording
Fantastic!! Man, this is a great recording of a GREAT show.  Both shows were outstanding, but this one stands out in my mind as well in my top 10 favorites.  Thanks for sharing this!!!

nice sound Nice sound!
Ramble on Rose - has a cut at 5:35 (Ouch!)

Was Healy really making upfront audience tapes???

Loser????? Hi. I originally was interested in this show (I'm not really into the post 74 retirement stuff normally), because I have a copy of the Jerry Garcia episode on some E Channel Biography of him when David Gans said something along the lines of , "I knew something was seriously wrong with the band when at a show in 82 when the band played Loser, and Jerry played a guitar solo that was one big ERROR. And the fact that that happened showed him and the band weren't communicating, and the fact that the crowd went nuts, showed they didnt really know any better"..or something very similar to that.. Now this is the only Loser they played at Ventura this year, could he really be talking about this one, as it seems ok to me.... Any comments???

about the recording or sound it's ok maybe high 3 or 4 but listening to the Wise/Miller i don't know kinda like it better it's a pretty tight show and i definately don't see anything wrong with the Loser Ventura was a killer place used to love places like that till the scene exploded then to stadiums love those old Cali theatres and such like Greek,Frost,Irvine even had fun on the soccer fields in Chula Vista 85 And Northridge in 90 thanks for re-kindling the spirit Internet Archives

Not this Loser I am not sure what Gans is talking about. I think not only is there nothing wrong with this Loser. It is one of my favorites. Jerry's solo combined with Phil's bass work make for a thundering, haunting version of this tune. In fact I used to listen to this particular version when I was in college in the 80's and I recently spent a few days hunting it down on this site. I remember it particularly for Jerry's solo and Phil's bass bombs. To each his own I guess. Gans at times is a little too impressed with himself for my liking anyway. This particular recording is great for an FOB.
Ventura We were at Ventura that weekend and the Loser from 7/18 is still one of my favorite versions I ever saw them play....
